Our insights into space: the most important telescopes
The telescope is said to have been invented by Hans Lipperhey in 1608 - even before Galileo Galilei used it for stargazing a year later.
Since then, the mirrors of optical telescopes have gotten bigger and bigger - and the insights they provide deeper and deeper.
